tmjmenu (1.3.4-2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Pin/Unpin runtime via right-click:
      - Dock: right-click num app pinado → desafixa imediatamente.
      - Popup search: right-click numa row → toggle pin (estrela
        aparece pra apps pinados).
  * Persistência em ~/.config/tmjmenu/pinned.json (atomic write).
  * Dock auto-reload via GFileMonitor: mudanças no JSON refletem
    sem precisar restart do tmjdock (pin do popup atualiza a dock
    automaticamente).
  * Novo botão "Show all apps" (view-app-grid-symbolic) entre o
    botão TMJOs e o separador. Click abre o Activities Overview do
    GNOME Shell via D-Bus (org.gnome.Shell.ShowApplications).
  * Super+Space keybinding configurado pelo /usr/bin/tmjmenu-first-run
    (autostart). gsettings custom-keybinding pra abrir tmjmenu.
    Idempotente — re-rodar não duplica.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 17:15:00 -0300

tmjmenu (1.3.4-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial .deb release of TMJMenu + TMJDock — the TMJOs proprietary
    application launcher stack.
  * Two binaries shipped in one package:
      - tmjmenu: popup search launcher (Super key trigger)
      - tmjdock: bottom-center dock with TMJOs central button
  * GTK4 + libadwaita + python-xlib (X11 dock hints: type=DOCK,
    strut_partial, monitor positioning).
  * Postinst disables /etc/xdg/autostart/plank.desktop if present,
    enables /etc/xdg/autostart/tmjdock.desktop. Plank package itself
    is left installed (tmjos-dock scripts like tmjos-first-run keep
    working).
  * Wayland deferred to v2.0 (gtk4-layer-shell).

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Mon, 11 May 2026 16:30:00 -0300
